President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Vermont due to severe storms and flooding that occurred from August 3 to August 5, 2023. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. William F. Roy of FEMA will coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA news desk.